The paper deals with a geometric problem of finding a point on a line in Euclidean spaces, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem is an online competitive algorithm problem, which involves designing algorithms with worst-case guarantees, and hence could also be categorized under data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves analyzing the competitive ratio of the algorithm, which could fall under game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves sequences of lines, which could be analyzed using techniques from discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm that improves upon the previous best-known bound, which could be categorized under algorithms and complexity (cs.SI).
